Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer, Delivery* with *Squarespace*. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend and platform engineering, specializing in CI/CD automation and GitOps, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the rigorous demands of infrastructure engineering and developer experience at scale*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed an AI-assisted delivery tooling layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls — helping engineers self-serve and diagnose build failures across 1,000+ platform endpoints. To improve implementation correctness across distributed environments, I architected generative CI/CD templates using GitHub Actions and Drone, alongside GitOps workflows with Helm charts and Argo CD. I also implemented a robust observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, reducing end-to-end delivery latency by 60% through targeted pipeline performance optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed and developed a cloud-native Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles high-volume file operations across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage. I also standardized Kubernetes deployment patterns and rollout/rollback workflows using AWS Step Functions, ensuring operational stability for long-running data jobs — both of which required *the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *build and evolve the platform that ships Squarespace services to production via CI/CD pipelines and GitOps workflows* and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *Squarespace's culture of rapid iteration and high-quality, design-driven engineering*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed Kubernetes-based HPC clusters for model training using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA, ensuring efficient resource allocation and high-performance CI/CD pipeline execution. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on building automated workflows with LangChain and LangGraph for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly — directly mirroring *the technical documentation and mentorship required to empower engineers to self-serve and diagnose platform failures*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *the Squarespace Delivery team and its mission to build opinionated paved roads for engineering*.


I have always been passionate about *helping people with creative ideas stand out and succeed* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *creating a future where everyone can be an entrepreneur*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

